# Auth & Session Rules

## Session Shape
- Session is extended in `global.d.ts` — add new session fields there, not inline.
- Available session fields: `isLoggedIn: boolean`, `user: UserDocument`.
- Always call `req.session.save()` before redirecting after mutating session state.

## Auth Flow
- All auth logic lives in `controllers/auth.controller.ts` + `routes/auth.routes.ts`.
- Routes: `GET/POST /login`, `GET /logout`, `GET/POST /signup`, `GET/POST /reset`, `GET/POST /reset-password`.
- `postLogin`: validates email + password (via `UserModel.isValidEmail` / `isPasswordLengthIsOk`), compares bcrypt hash, sets session, redirects to `/admin/products`.
- `postSignup`: validates fields, checks `UserModel.isUserExistByEmail`, hashes passwords with `bcrypt`, saves user, sends welcome email via `NodeMailModel.sendWelcomeEmail`.
- `postReset`: validates email, fetches user via `UserModel.getUserByEmail`, creates JWT token (`NodeMailModel.createResetPasswordToken`), saves `TokenModel`, sends reset email.
- `getResetPassword`: verifies token via `NodeMailModel.verifyResetPasswordToken`, renders form with `_email` and `_token` locals.
- `postResetPassword`: finds user by `_email`, hashes new passwords, saves, deletes `TokenModel` record, redirects to `/login`.
- `getLogout`: destroys session, redirects to `/`.

## Password Security
- Always hash with `bcrypt.hash(password, 12)` — never store plain text.
- Compare with `bcrypt.compareSync(plain, hashed)` in `postLogin`.

## Flash Messages
- Use `req.flash('error', '...')` for errors and `req.flash('success', '...')` for success.
- `res.locals.error` and `res.locals.success` are set globally in the locals middleware; views read from those.

## Middleware
- `req.user` is populated for every request in `app.ts` via `UserModel.findById(req.session?.user?._id)`.
- Do not duplicate user-loading logic in controllers — use `req.user` directly.
- `res.locals.userName` is also set in the locals middleware for displaying the signed-in user badge in navigation.

## Do Not
- Do not store raw passwords — always use `bcrypt`.
- Do not bypass `req.session.save()` before a redirect when session state changes.
- Do not expose `/admin` handlers outside `isAuth` protected route mounting.
- Do not call `UserModel.isValidEmail` / `UserModel.isPasswordLengthIsOk` only in controllers — they are static methods on the model.

